cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "NLE-Bench: Feasibility-Aware Tool Use in Symbolic Non-Linear Video Editing"
message: "If you use this benchmark in your research, please cite the paper."
type: dataset
authors:
  - name: "Anonymous (identity withheld for double-blind review)"
abstract: |
  NLE-Bench is an 800-scenario benchmark for evaluating tool-use agents on
  symbolic non-linear editing project states. Scenarios are organized as
  a 4 (perception) x 4 (execution) factorial of feasible scenarios (640)
  plus 80 infeasible and 80 ambiguous calibration scenarios. Each scenario provides a
  natural-language instruction, an initial EditProject state (JSON), a
  constraint set (YAML) for deterministic scoring, and taxonomy labels.
  This artifact release uses the frozen v3.1 scenario-corpus snapshot,
  where v3.1 is a corpus provenance label rather than the public benchmark
  release number.
keywords:
  - tool-use agents
  - LLM evaluation
  - benchmark
  - agent calibration
  - abstention
  - clarification
  - video editing
  - constraint satisfaction
  - refusal
